## CONFIDENCE SCALE

All confidence fields (`*_confidence`) use this scale. Record an integer 0–10.

| Score | Anchor Label | Meaning |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| 0 | No basis for classification | Critical information entirely absent; field cannot be populated |
| 1–2 | Very low confidence | Major ambiguity or inference required; multiple plausible interpretations |
| 3–4 | Low confidence | Significant gaps; at least one key piece of information is missing or unclear |
| 5 | Moderate confidence | Some explicit evidence, but meaningful inference required |
| 6–7 | Good confidence | Mostly explicit information; minor ambiguity only |
| 8–9 | High confidence | All key information explicit and unambiguous |
| 10 | Complete confidence | Every field in this block directly and unambiguously stated in the text |

Every confidence rating must be accompanied by its paired `*_rationale` field explaining specifically why that score was assigned — what was explicit, what required inference, and what was absent.

