## RULES

1. Complete `thinking_chain_of_thought` in full before completing any other field. Minimum 300 words. Address all 8 sub-questions. Only think within the allocated thinking JSON field.
2. Base all extractions on explicit textual evidence. Do not infer values not derivable from the text unless an explicit inference rule is stated in these instructions.
3. Do not add, rename, or omit any fields from the JSON schema.
4. Use `null` for any numeric or string field where the value is not reported and cannot be determined. Use `[]` for empty arrays. Never use `""` in place of null.
5. N = participants in the final analyses. Follow the N extraction rules exactly. Do not record the initially enrolled sample unless no final N is reported.
6. Gender: record whichever metric (% or raw N) the article provides. Do not calculate the other. Never code "no response / elected not to respond" as gender minority.
7. Method classification: Experimental requires both random assignment AND a manipulation explicitly stated. If unsure between two adjacent codes, default to the less controlled category. Note the ambiguity.
8. Sub-studies (2A, 2B) are separate entries in `structure_studies` with their own `study_id`.
9. `meta_author_first_last`: last name of first author + last name of last author, no space. Single-author paper: repeat the last name.
10. Confidence is an integer 0–10. Use the anchor scale. Every confidence field requires its paired rationale field.
11. Excluded articles (screen_include_exclude = 2): extract Domain 1 metadata fully. Leave `structure_studies` as `[]`. Set all structure, demo, setting, and method fields to their null/empty/zero equivalents.
12. Shared samples: set `structure_shared_sample_flag = true`, note in `study_n_notes` for the affected studies, and ensure `structure_total_n_mothership` reflects unique participants only.

